The Annie Lennox Collection is the first greatest hits compilation by Scottish singer-songwriter Annie Lennox. It was released on March 2009 and also contains two newly recorded songs, "Shining Light", originally a single by Ash, and a cover of Keane's rare B-side "Closer Now", retitled "Pattern of My Life". The artwork was shot by rock singer Bryan Adams.
